Keep dedicated shell environments out of the root Emacs event loop.

The optional child bindings are inert for interactive/ordinary Anvil.  A
dedicated backend can provide immutable child environment, exec-path, and
shell values; anvil-host applies them only around make-process so timers and
concurrent requests run under the root daemon's baseline environment.

--- a/anvil-host.el
